New Records: Harry Brook scored 312 runs as captain in a bilateral ODI series vs Australia, the most by any captain in such a series.
Key Match Events: Australia won by 49 runs (DLS) and secured the series 3-2.
Ben Duckett scored a century with 107 runs.
Travis Head took four wickets and scored 31 runs.
Harry Brook hit six sixes in nine balls.
Adil Rashid's innings ended with 36 runs.
England collapsed from 202 for 2 to 309 all out.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia won the toss and chose to bowl.
Teams in brief: no Jofra Archer for England, no Alex Carey for Australia.
Post-Match Reflections: Australia's spinners squeezed the life out of England, leading to their collapse.
The rain played a significant role, arriving just five balls too late to save England.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play multiple times, affecting the match.
The match was played with an eye on the weather, impacting strategies.
